<p class="">This point is really fundamental to the Bill. Does not the right hon. Gentleman see that there is a conflict between object and method; that no one would disagree with the objects as set out in paragraph (<em>c</em>) of Clause 1 (1) of the Bill, but what the House demands is that they should know what methods are to be taken to achieve those objects?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-666edfe3-3001-4a2e-a2db-ab5e43b834bf" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
